President Obama delivered a speech in Jacksonville, Florida on the seventh anniversary of the Recovery Act. He began by addressing the recent mass shootings in Kansas and Michigan, expressing his condolences and calling for action to prevent such tragedies. The President then discussed the progress made since the financial crisis, highlighting the creation of 14 million new jobs and the decrease in unemployment rate. He also mentioned improvements in education, healthcare coverage, and the clean energy industry. The President emphasized the importance of the Recovery Act in stabilizing the economy and investing in renewable energy. He praised Saft America, a company that manufactures advanced batteries, as an example of the success of clean energy investments. The President concluded by urging continued efforts to build a stronger economy and create more opportunities for the American people.